  "prompt": "How many valves are present in a 4 stroke engine?",
  "response": "In a typical 4-stroke internal combustion engine, there are generally **two valves per cylinder**: one **intake valve** and one **exhaust valve**. However, some engines, especially high-performance or modern designs, may have **four valves per cylinder** (two intake and two exhaust valves) to improve efficiency and power output.\n\nSo, the total number of valves in a 4-stroke engine depends on the number of cylinders and the valve configuration:\n\n- **2 valves per cylinder**: Total valves = 2 \u00d7 number of cylinders\n- **4 valves per cylinder**: Total valves = 4 \u00d7 number of cylinders\n\nFor example:\n- A 4-cylinder engine with 2 valves per cylinder has **8 valves**.\n- A 4-cylinder engine with 4 valves per cylinder has **16 valves**.",
